{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "sdlc-api-collection-v1",
    "name": "SDLC.ai API v1",
    "description": "Comprehensive API collection for the SDLC.ai Secure Data Learning Platform\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. **Authentication**: Run the \"Auth - Login\" request first to obtain a JWT token\n2. **Environment Variables**: Make sure the following variables are set in your environment:\n   - `base_url`: API base URL (e.g., https://api.sdlc.cc/v1)\n   - `jwt_token`: Will be automatically set after login\n   - `tenant_id`: Your tenant ID\n3. **Test Execution**: Use the \"SDLC API Tests\" collection runner to execute all tests\n\n## Collection Structure\n\n- **Authentication**: Login, logout, token refresh\n- **Tenant Management**: CRUD operations for tenants\n- **User Management**: User operations and role management\n- **Documents**: Document upload, processing, and management\n- **RAG**: Query documents and get AI-powered responses\n- **Vector Search**: Semantic and hybrid search\n- **DLP**: Data loss prevention scanning\n- **Monitoring**: Health checks and metrics\n\n## Test Scripts\n\nEach request includes test scripts that:\n- Validate response status codes\n- Check response structure\n- Save tokens for subsequent requests\n- Measure response times\n- Log test results\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nRequired variables:\n- `base_url`: API base URL\n- `tenant_id`: Tenant identifier\n- `user_email`: User email for login\n- `user_password`: User password\n\nAutomatically set:\n- `jwt_token`: JWT access token\n- `refresh_token`: JWT refresh token\n- `user_id`: Current user ID\n\n## Notes\n\n- All requests include proper error handling\n- Rate limiting headers are automatically checked\n- Tests are designed to work with the mock server or real API\n- Some requests may require additional permissions based on user role",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "sdlc-platform"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{jwt_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Global pre-request script",
          "// Add timestamp to all requests for tracking",
          pm.request.headers.add({",
          "    key: 'X-Request-ID',",
          "    value: 'req_' + Date.now() + '_' + Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9)",
          "    disabled: false",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Add client version",
          "pm.request.headers.add({",
          "    key: 'X-Client-Version',",
          "    value: '1.0.0',",
          "    disabled: false",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Add client name",
          "pm.request.headers.add({",
          "    key: 'X-Client-Name',",
          "    value: 'Postman',",
          "    disabled: false",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Log request details",
          "console.log('[' + pm.info.requestName + '] Sending request to:', pm.request.url.toString());",
          "",
          "// Check if token is expired",
          "if (pm.collectionVariables.get('jwt_token') && pm.collectionVariables.get('token_expires_at')) {",
          "    var expiresAt = parseInt(pm.collectionVariables.get('token_expires_at'));",
          "    var now = Date.now();",
          "    ",
          "    if (now >= expiresAt) {",
          "        console.log('Token expired, attempting refresh...');",
          "        // Token refresh would be handled in a separate request",
          "    }",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Global test script",
          "",
          "// Check response status",
          "pm.test('Status code is successful', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201, 202, 204]);",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Check response time",
          "pm.test('Response time is less than 2 seconds', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Log response details",
          "console.log('[' + pm.info.requestName + '] Response:', {",
          "    status: pm.response.code,",
          "    time: pm.response.responseTime,",
          "    size: pm.response.responseSize",
          "});",
          "",
          "// Check rate limiting headers",
          "if (pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Limit')) {",
          "    pm.test('Rate limiting headers present', function () {",
          "        pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Limit')).to.exist;",
          "        pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Remaining')).to.exist;",
          "    });",
          "    ",
          "    // Log rate limit info",
          "    console.log('Rate Limit:', {",
          "        limit: pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Limit'),",
          "        remaining: pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Remaining'),",
          "        reset: pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Reset')",
          "    });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
